<div class="panel-body list-group collapse out" data-propname="RisksOfTest" id="article-RisksOfTest" role="tabpanel" style="display: none;">
<h2>Does the scan carry any risks?</h2>
<p>A gastric emptying scan involves giving a very small amount of radiation to your child. The nuclear medicine team will discuss this with you when you and your child arrive for the scan. You might also find it helpful to read this <a href="http://www.imagegently.org/Roles-What-can-I-do/Parent/Nuclear-Medicine" target="_blank">information about nuclear medicine</a> from the Alliance for Radiation Safety in Pediatric Imaging.</p> </div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div aria-controls="article-PreparingForProcedure" aria-expanded="false" class="panel-heading clickable rs_preserve" role="button" tabindex="0">
<span class="panel-heading-collapsable">Preparing for the test</span>
<span class="pull-right panel-heading-collapsable-icon" href="#article-PreparingForProcedure">
<i aria-hidden="true" class="mdi mdi-chevron-down"></i>
</span>
</div>
<div class="panel-body list-group collapse out" data-propname="PreparingForProcedure" id="article-PreparingForProcedure" role="tabpanel" style="display: none;">
<h2>Does my child need to do anything special to prepare for the scan?</h2>
<p>Your child will not be able to eat or drink anything for a while before the scan, even food that is not normally swallowed (such as chewing gum or sucking candy).</p>
<ul>
<li>For a solid scan, your child must not eat or drink anything four to six hours before the test.</li>
<li>For a liquid scan, your child must not eat or drink anything three to four hours before the test.</li>
</ul> </div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div aria-controls="article-Procedure" aria-expanded="false" class="panel-heading clickable rs_preserve" role="button" tabindex="0">
<span class="panel-heading-collapsable">Test</span>
